00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:44,500
right?

171
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:45,580
Okay.

172
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:50,380
If I rolled it across the surface of a sphere,

173
00:06:50,380 --> 00:06:53,080
it would move as straight as possible along the surface.

174
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:55,300
Along the surface of a geodesic,

175
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:57,400
in that case a great circle.

176
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:59,900
So this is an experiment.

177
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:01,160
Well,

178
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,600
I suppose you'd say the wheels stick

179
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:04,040
out of the surface a little bit,

180
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:08,130
but we could make the whole thing smaller and

181
00:07:08,130 --> 00:07:12,180
smaller until the dumbbell bug here was infinitely small,

182
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,170
and allow him to sweep

183
00:07:15,170 --> 00:07:17,140
out geodesics across the surface here.

184
00:07:20,420 --> 00:07:22,320
So the idea of a geodesic,

185
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:24,120
and not only the idea of a geodesic,

186
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:26,940
but the idea of parallel transport

187
00:07:26,940 --> 00:07:29,660
and the idea of covariant derivative,

188
00:07:30,060 --> 00:07:31,920
are ideas which are intrinsic.

189
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:34,160
Intrinsic,

190
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:36,660
that bug could move around.

191
00:07:37,380 --> 00:07:38,380
Of course,

192
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:40,040
we're really thinking about ourselves

193
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,700
as bugs in three dimensions,

194
00:07:41,980 --> 00:07:44,460
and we're trying to disconnect

195
00:07:44,460 --> 00:07:46,940
the intrinsic properties of three-dimensional space

196
00:07:46,940 --> 00:07:49,340
from the possibility that it might

197
00:07:49,340 --> 00:07:51,740
perhaps be embedded in some fourth dimension,

198
00:07:51,740 --> 00:07:52,820
or something like that.

199
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:53,680
Well,

200
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:56,340
we wouldn't want to use rollers,

201
00:07:56,620 --> 00:07:58,360
but we could use gyroscopes.

202
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,610
And gyroscopes are things which only

203
00:08:00,610 --> 00:08:02,860
point in our own three-dimensional space.

204
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:06,600
They don't point out into any hypothetical fourth dimension.

205
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:11,400
And so exploring space with gyroscopes,

206
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:13,160
and rulers,

207
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,480
and so forth,

208
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,570
would be exploring the

209
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:18,540
intrinsic geometry of three-dimensional space.

210
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,020
In any case,

211
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:21,620
one of the things we can do,

212
00:08:21,740 --> 00:08:23,100
with gyroscopes,

213
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:25,380
is we can define parallel transport.

214
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:28,240
A gyroscope will naturally move in

215
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:30,580
a way which moves parallel to itself,

216
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:32,539
and it does define parallel transport,

217
00:08:32,539 --> 00:08:33,380
physically.

218
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:36,640
It has the same properties as

219
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:39,000
the parallel transport that we describe mathematically.

220
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:41,380
In any case,

221
00:08:41,380 --> 00:08:44,720
we can proceed to parallelly transport that vector

222
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,020
from one point to another,

223
00:08:47,540 --> 00:08:47,880
and,

224
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:48,720
in fact,

225
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:49,940
around in a closed curve.

226
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:52,280
When it goes around in a closed curve,

227
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:55,540
it will not necessarily come back to the same configuration.

228
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:59,180
What'll happen to it is it will rotate in general.

229
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:04,040
Parallel transport does not change the length of vectors.

230
00:09:05,180 --> 00:09:08,260
It changes only their orientation.

231
00:09:08,820 --> 00:09:11,720
It does not change their length.

232
00:09:12,540 --> 00:09:13,280
And so,

233
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:14,240
at most,

234
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,420
what can happen to a vector

235
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:16,420
is when it comes around,

236
00:09:16,420 --> 00:09:18,380
it gets rotated by some angle.

237
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:21,440
Okay.

238
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:24,200
Now,

239
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,160
there are two senses of rotation

240
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:28,120
that we have to keep track of.

241
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:28,580
Senses,

242
00:09:28,580 --> 00:09:30,640
I mean now senses in the sense of sign,

243
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:31,520
S-I-G-N.

244
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:33,720
First of all,

245
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:36,500
there's the direction that we go around the loop.

246
00:09:37,780 --> 00:09:40,540
We can go around one way or the other way.

247
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:43,420
Depending on which way we go around,

248
00:09:44,139 --> 00:09:45,969
the vector will either shift in

249
00:09:45,969 --> 00:09:47,800
one direction or in the other direction.

250
00:09:48,540 --> 00:09:50,230
That's one sense of angle that

251
00:09:50,230 --> 00:09:51,920
we have to keep track of,

252
00:09:52,060 --> 00:09:54,720
which direction we circumnavigated around.

253
00:09:54,860 --> 00:09:56,900
We took our vector and we went around,

254
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:57,640
let's say,

255
00:09:57,660 --> 00:09:58,980
let's say counterclockwise.

256
00:09:59,820 --> 00:10:02,260
The other angle that we need to keep track of

257
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:05,960
is the amount that the angle deviates.

258
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:07,520
So,

259
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:08,100
for example,

260
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:11,660
if we go around counterclockwise

261
00:10:13,020 --> 00:10:14,660
and the vector,

262
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:17,440
as it's transported around the curve,

263
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:20,740
gets deflected in the counterclockwise direction,

264
00:10:23,180 --> 00:10:26,070
counterclockwise excursion

265
00:10:26,070 --> 00:10:28,960
produces counterclockwise rotation,

266
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,820
then we say that the curvature is positive.

267
00:10:32,610 --> 00:10:35,665
If counterclockwise excursion produces

268
00:10:35,665 --> 00:10:38,720
clockwise rotation of the vector,

269
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:40,920
we say the curvature is negative.

270
00:10:42,460 --> 00:10:44,260
Whatever the curvature is,

271
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:47,000
it's a single function

272
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:48,940
on the space,

273
00:10:49,220 --> 00:10:50,910
and it's simply defined by

274
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:52,600
going around with your little probe,

275
00:10:55,260 --> 00:10:55,860
measuring,

276
00:10:55,860 --> 00:10:59,160
let's by definition say we go around counterclockwise,

277
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:01,100
we measure the angle.

278
00:11:01,540 --> 00:11:02,360
For small,

279
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,140
for very,

280
00:11:03,140 --> 00:11:06,140
very small curves here,

281
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:08,040
the angle will be small.

282
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:10,460
So let's just call it d theta,

283
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:12,900
the small change in the angle

284
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:14,900
when we go around the closed loop.

